{
  "text": "Now we create an application stack that references the network stack. We use Pulumi's stack reference to get outputs from the network stack. This creates an implicit dependency. The application stack depends on the network stack. We can then use these reference values to create resources in the existing VPC. For example, we create EC2 instances using the ObsistingNet IDs from the network stack, and we attach security groups that were created in the network stack. This modular approach makes it easy to update networking applications, and vice versa.",
